-- Canada New House Price Index Advances 0.1% on Calgary Increase
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-10-10T12:30:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-10/canada-new-house-price-index-advances-0-1-on-calgary-increase.html
Canada ’s new home  price index  rose
0.1 percent in August from July on gains in Calgary, trailing
the median forecast in an economist survey, the government
statistics agency said.  Calgary prices climbed 0.6 percent in August on labor,
material and land costs, Statistics Canada said today in Ottawa.
Prices in Toronto, Canada’s largest city, were little changed on
the month. Economists predicted the index would rise 0.2
percent, according to the median of eight forecasts in a
Bloomberg  survey .  Ottawa home prices registered the first annual drop since
January 1998, falling 0.2 percent. Prices in the National
Capital Region, which includes Ottawa and Gatineau, Quebec
declined 0.1 percent in August from July. Finance Minister  Jim
Flaherty  introduced a plan to reduce the federal government’s
workforce in his last budget.  Ottawa’s decline contrasted with the nationwide increase of
1.8 percent in August from a year ago, including advances of 6.1
percent in Calgary and 2.2 percent in Toronto. Vancouver prices
declined 1.3 percent on the year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
